    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13340#discussion_r3230023811\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>so a tiny crate that we use in wasmtime</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>FWIW, I'd reuse the existing <code>crates/core</code> (possibly with a new <code>runtime</code> feature or something) and have <code>crates/examples/mpk_available.rs</code> as the binary. This avoids the hassle of new crates (which requires crossing some Ts and dotting some Is) and also makes it something that isn't built unless the user really wants it.</p>\n</blockquote>",
