    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13340#pullrequestreview-4284449694\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594930376,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778697776
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13340#discussion_r3236658424\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>While I realize that Cargo has no way of splitting this up, personally I don't think this is viable to add to CI. If a new test is added to the <code>wasmtime-cli</code> crate it'll never get run on CI because it's not mentioned here, and we basically have no way of knowing that (it's pretty unlikely someone checks CI logs to ensure the test is being run).</p>\n<p>I don't really know of a great answer for this otherwise. The only other thing I can think of is to move test suites around to keep the \"single crate buckets\" from before as still just crates. For example we could create a dedicated crate to just doing the <code>*.wast</code> tests and leave the <code>all</code> test where it is. Or... something like that.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 594930377,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778697776
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> fitzgen submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13340#pullrequestreview-4284587943\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 594934213,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778699003
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> fitzgen created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13340#discussion_r3236780460\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We can use <code>cargo metadata</code> and parse the JSON output to get all <code>test</code> targets for a crate.</p>\n</blockquote>",
